<li id="cite_note-36"><b><a href="#cite_ref-36" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.ftc.gov/os/caselist/0523047/0523047.shtm" class="external text" title="http://www.ftc.gov/os/caselist/0523047/0523047.shtm" rel="nofollow">United States of America (for the Federal Trade Commission) Plaintiff, v. TJ Web Productions, LLC, Civil Action No.: ********, FTC File No. 052-3047</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-37"><b><a href="#cite_ref-37" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.ftc.gov/os/caselist/0423180/0423180.shtm" class="external text" title="http://www.ftc.gov/os/caselist/0423180/0423180.shtm" rel="nofollow">United States of America (for the Federal Trade Commission) Plaintiff, v. BangBros.com, Inc., a Florida Corporation, RK Netmedia, Inc., a Florida Corporation, OX Ideas, Inc., and a Florida Corporation, Civil Action No.: ********, FTC File No. 042-3180</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-38"><b><a href="#cite_ref-38" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://docs.justia.com/cases/federal/district-courts/washington/wawdce/2:2005cv01285/129006/38/" class="external text" title="http://docs.justia.com/cases/federal/district-courts/washington/wawdce/2:2005cv01285/129006/38/" rel="nofollow">Court denies summary judgment</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-39"><b><a href="#cite_ref-39" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://seattlepi.nwsource.com/business/356247_spam25.html" class="external text" title="http://seattlepi.nwsource.com/business/356247_spam25.html" rel="nofollow">Adult Web business off the hook for spam</a></li>
</ol>
<ul>
<li>Lee, Younghwa (June 2005). "The CAN-SPAM Act: A Silver Bullet Solution?". <i>Communications of the ACM</i>, p. 131–132.</li>
</ul>
